Today, more than three years after the bombardment, little more is known than at that time, yes, the puzzles became rather larger in time.
Former US President George W. Bush recently revealed in his memoirs that the CIA was quite certain that Syria was building a reactor in el-Kibar before the attack, but saw little evidence that there was "an active nuclear weapons program" in the country.
Some secret service workers in Europe prefer to be even more cautious and only speak of an "alleged reactor", even if they think the CIA presentation is "plausible".
