The United States amends the rules for obtaining a visa
Before talking to the consulate, people must present themselves at the visa application service points and costs will be reduced.
From 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa at the United States Embassy and Consulates will change.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves to the visa application service points (ASC, the initial letters in English) prior to their conversation at the consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be verified by the consulate prior to the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for aspirants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa is reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment, processing the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the counter to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only wish to extend their visa do not have to have a conversation at the consulate, they only have to imagine at the nearest ASC, where they will present their documents and take their fingerprints.
Since the biometric data are collected at the ASC, applicants who need a second appointment for the conversation at the consulate remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa at the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service supplement of 26 dollars.
Further information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembasy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas FAQs.html
