Second, the idea that a hacker can tap into the most secret secrets of the most powerful country in the world is a major blow to the prestige of the state department.
In addition, the scandal brings less victims than the "sharpening judges".
But let us devote ourselves to the profound nature of what has happened.
Formerly, in Orwell's time, all power could be bundled together like a Big Brother who controlled every gesture of his subjects.
Since then, Orwell's prophecy could have turned out to be perfectly correct, where you can control every movement thanks to the phone, every transaction made, the hotel visited, the chosen highway and so on; the citizen would become the total victim of the eye of power.
